On Sat, 23 Jul 2005, Access Systems wrote:

> On Sat, 23 Jul 2005, Don Tuleja wrote:
>
> > It's the stupid stripped out intake stud. The small amount of JB I put
> > in there didn't cut it.
>
> use a new unstripped stud,  put some steelwool (not soap kind, but
> carpenters kind) very small amount, take your JB weld and put some into
> the hole, now screw in the stud.
>   go on vacation.  when you get back you should have a dern near good as
> new stud.

For all this trouble, it seems to me that it would be better to either
install a stepped stud or an insert.

Despite its name, JB weld is simply an epoxy.  Epoxies cannot be expected
to maintain their strength at the temperatures experienced in a head,
even when reinforced with steel wool.

Do the job right and you won't have to do it again!

George
